	<title>Math340Fa24-FinalExam</title>
	<introduction>
		<p>
			Notation reminders: <m>M_{mn}</m> is the vector space of <m>m\times n</m> real matrices with standard matrix addition and scalar multiplication, <m>P_d</m> is the vector space of polynomials (in <m>x</m>) of degree at most <m>d</m> with standard polynomial addition and scalar multiplication, <m>\mathbf{0}</m> denotes the zero vector in a vector space <m>V</m>. <m>\mathbb{R}^n</m> uses the standard vector addition/scalar multiplication and dot product unless otherwise noted.
		</p>
		<p>
			Additional notation reminders: <m>O</m> denotes the zero matrix, and <m>I_n</m> denotes the <m>n\times n</m> identity matrix. <m>\text{tr}(A)</m> denotes the trace of a matrix <m>A</m>.
		</p>
	</introduction>
	<exercise points="7">
		<introduction>
			<p>
				Consider <m>T:P_2\to P_1</m> by <m>T(p(x))=p(0)+2p'(x)</m>. You can assume that <m>T</m> is a linear transformation.
			</p>
			<p>
				Find <m>M_{DB}(T)</m>, where <m>B=(5,x^2+3,x)</m> and <m>D=(1,x)</m>. Show all work.<!-- linebreak -->(Hint: your final matrix will be <m>2\times 3</m>).
			</p>
		</introduction>
	</exercise>
